result.execSummary:
The defendant Nathan M. Hanson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).
  • Theft-Movable Property-Special Facts [Modifiers: as a Party to a Crime], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).
  • Theft-Movable Property-Special Facts [Modifiers: as a Party to a Crime], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).
  • Theft-Movable Property-Special Facts [Modifiers: as a Party to a Crime], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
The restitution includes the read-ins of Taylor County Cases 16CF117 and 16CF32.  The restitution in this case is joint and several with Taylor County cases 16CF47 and 16CF50.  The restitution for the read-in Taylor County case 16CF32 is joint and several with Taylor County case 16CF43.  The restitution in the read-in Taylor County case 16CF117 is joint and several with Taylor County cases 16CF118 and 16CF119.
The cash bond of $1,000.00 was applied as follows:  $750.00 to the victim in Case No. 16CF117 and $250.00 to the victim in Case No. 16CF28.
Defendant shall submit a DNA sample to the Taylor County Sheriff's Department.

Defendant shall undergo counseling as deemed appropriate by probation.  Defendant shall obtain his GED/HSED or adult Diploma through the Medford Adult Diploma Academy.  Defendant shall have no contact with his co-defendants and the victims and their family members.  Defendant shall pay supervision fees as ordered by the Department of Corrections. 
If probation is ordered and ultimately revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used.
Defendant shall undergo an AODA and follow through with any recommendations.

timeConds.notes:
The jail sentence shall begin no later than May 14, 2017 at 4:30 pm.  The defendant shall pay all sheriff and jail fees or costs allowed or imposed by law and the sheriff shall be entitled to a judgment against the defendant for any such unpaid fees or costs.  
Jail can be served in any county in the State of Wisconsin provided arrangements are made by counsel or the defendant, it is approved by the Taylor County Jail, and at no additional cost to Taylor County.

Concurrent with: Taylor County Case 16CF26
